recordings.file-name: XC282133-delichon urbicum 2 real de la jara 17-06-2015.mp3
recordings.rmk: Un macho cantando sobre los restos de su nido derrumbado, es realmente triste, se ve que los dueños lo tiraron porque ensucian los pollos con sus heces. No sé si le había dado tiempo a criar este año y se lo habían tirado después, lo cual dudo, o bien lo había intentado construir varias veces y se lo tiraron repetidamente, más probable. Grabado en el mismo Real de la Jara, un pequeño pueblo de la sierra.

Songscape de aviones comunes no sabemos exactamente si comiendo tan sólo, disponiéndose a dormir en el lugar por ser individuos ya exentos de la reproducción o que había nidos en la zona que no vimos. Un talud rocoso cortado casi vertical. En Los alrededores hay serranía escarpada con Pinus alepensis y suelo calizo con matorral propio de este terreno, y una de las particularidades del lugar es que hay un abundante sotobosque de palmito y romero.

I initially considered a possible Temminck's Stint flight call, the species occurs here regularily. After some research, the sonograph seems to clearly show that the call is too high pitched for this species normal trilling flight call and I am currently stumped as to the identity of the caller. The call was picked up by an unattended Parabol that had been left out recording overnight. The location is a Baltic coastal island far to the north, the parabol was directed over the water towards the mainland to attempt to record and migrating wader or other species.
Edit; Latter solved as House Martin flight call.

recordings.ssp: Hybrid House Martin x Barn Swallow
recordings.rmk: Composite recording with two calls from a juvenile hybrid House Martin x Barn Swallow. The bird was associated with a brood of Barn Swallows. Some of its apparent siblings were fed by an adult Barn Swallow. The hybrid was not seen being fed, but it was begging together with the juvenile Barn Swallows. The heard calls were very similar to those of the juvenile Barn Swallows. Photos of the bird can be found at https://www.artportalen.se/Image/2151098
